lyze business requirements by partnering with key stakeholders across the organization to develop solutions for business needs Responsible for bringing technology improvements and enhancements in support of the paperless, automation vision Design and implement new network solutions and/or improving the efficiency of current networks Install, configure and support network equipment including routers, proxy servers, switches, WAN accelerators, DNS and DHCPProcure network equipment and managing subcontractors involved with network installation Configure firewalls, routing and switching to maximize network efficiency and security Maximize network performance through ongoing monitoring and troubleshooting Arrange scheduled upgrades and investigate faults in network Update network equipment to the latest firmware releases and report network status to key stakeholders Requirements Bachelor\'s or Master\'s degree in Computer Science/IT or equivalent Computer Certifications is advantageous (CCNA/CCNP, AWS Office 365, Cyber Security, VMWARE, ARUBA or similar)Proven experience in a similar role is a must Excellent presentation and communication skills Ability to work in a fast-paced dynamic environment Strong stakeholder management skills Benefits Competitive salary + standard benefits',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Allsopp & Allsopp Recruitment',NULL),('Data Analyst Specialist','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:- Defining new data collection and analysis processes.- Data collection, data filtration, data cleaning, updating and managing master data. - Processing confidential data and information according to guidelines. - Supporting initiatives for data integrity and normalization. - Interpret data, analyze results using statistical techniques and provide ongoing reports - Develop and implement databases, data collection systems, data analytics, data validations, data cleansing and other strategies that optimize statistica