ill be responsible of hiring for tecnical roles within the tech industry such as Devops, AWS, Java, Info-Sec among other roles and dealing with several clients. You will be leading the process from translating the brief into a sourcing strategy to maximize the possibility of placing the roles successfully. - Fluency in English is a MUST - Leadership skills and agility - Experience from 4-5 years  ',NULL,'2023-10-12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Antal International - Egypt',NULL),('Project Lead, Communications','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Responsibilities: Project Management: Lead the charge with the onsite team to deliver on the client\'s communication strategy and collaborate with the client team members. Ensure the delivery of the annual communication plan and develop next year’s annual plan. Develop full communication plans for activities on the client\'s grid. Manage multiple activities simultaneously, ensuring they are delivered on time, within budget, and meet client expectations. Coordinate tasks, timelines, and resources effectively. Ensuring the development of a comprehensive communication plan and timeline, including resource allocation and budget estimation for activities on the client\'s grid. Review and edit communication materials to ensure accuracy, clarity, and alignment with the client\'s requirements and messaging. Ensure adherence to brand guidelines and maintain consistent messaging. All social media material (infographic, posts, videos, etc.) All media material (PRLs, speeches, etc.) All creative material developed by the creative team and approved by the creative leadership Track campaign performance and effectiveness. Client Management: Build strong relationships with clients based on trust and effective communication. Understand the client\'s business, global trends, current events, and target audience to deliver impactful communication guidance. Establish strong relationships with key members of the Strategic Communications Department in addition to the client’s office. Communicate project updates, progress, and risks effectively to ensure alignment and obtain necessary approvals in a timely manner. Team Leadership: Lead and manage a cross-functional team, including assigning tasks, setting clear expectations, and providing guidance and support. Collaborate with internal teams, such as designers, writers, and digital specialists, to execute projects successfully. Assign tasks, provide guidance, and facilitate smooth teamwork. Provide guidance and feedback to the creative team assigned to the project and ensure that all creative materials align with the client\'s brand, messaging, and objectives. Foster a collaborative and motivated work environment to ensure team productivity and cohesion. Lead a daily huddle among all team members. Ensure all team members are adhering to the deployment plan. Support the project PMO is provided support when needed on project plan updates, client procurement matters, invoicing, etc. Report to the APCO Senior Strategic Lead weekly across all workstreams and client updates.  Escalate to the SSL any issues and risks if and as they occur. Competencies Excellent communication skills written and verbally Ability to multitask and work under pressure in a fast-paced environment Excellent organization and time management skills, strong attention to detail Knowledge development skills Initiative Teamwork skills Ability to be flexible, resilient, solution oriented and creative Service-orientated attitude, proactive thinker, information seeker Requirements Bachelor’s Degree in business administration, public administration or Equivalent 8-10 years of experience as a project manager in an agency, or in a Tech or governmental industry Experience working with PR or advertising/creative agency a plus Prior Content writing experience Fluency in English and Arabic Work Conditions The physical abilities needed to perform the duties of this position, in addition to the offi