ls and performance. Developing comprehensive training programs and materials to enhance the team\'s knowledge of dispatching procedures. Ensuring the team meets or exceeds service level agreements and key performance indicators related to dispatching. Maintaining open communication channels with team members and other departments to address issues and streamline dispatching processes. Handling escalated customer complaints and resolving issues promptly, with a strong focus on efficient task dispatching. Conducting regular team meetings to review performance, share best practices, and collaboratively identify areas of improvement. Demonstrating proficiency in dispatch programs such as Perspective or other relevant dispatching software. Utilizing hands-on experience with radio dispatch equipment to optimize task allocation and communication. Exhibiting the ability to deliver results under time constraints and meet deadlines in a fast-paced dispatching environment. Previous experience in terminal operations, dispatch, or as a driver, providing valuable insights into effective dispatching practices. Qualifications: Possession of a Bachelor\'s degree or equivalent experience in a related field. A minimum of 3-5 years of experience in a call center environment, with proven leadership experience. Fluency in English, enabling effective communication with offshore team members. Strong leadership abilities, coupled with effective coaching and mentoring skills. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to facilitate seamless collaboration within the team and across departments. Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, high-pressure environment, ensuring efficient task dispatching. Proficient analytical and problem-solving skills, enabling effective resolution of dispatching challenges. Knowledge of call center software and technology, particularly as it relates to dispatching. Flexibility to work flexible hours and weekends, as required by the offshore call center operation.'