ure compliance with codes, processes, QA/QC policies, performance requirements, and specifications;Coordinate project estimating and timeline with estimation team; Submit all essential documentation with bills to client/owner representative and sign off completion certificates;Maintain project Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) to organize and monitor project work scope; Perform other job-related activities as required. Qualifications Bachelor\'s degree in mechanical, marine, or similar engineering.15 years of Project Engineering experience from top construction companies MS Office, Auto CAD, and engineering software skills Fluent in English. Mechanical, structural, and SURF knowledge',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'BD SELECT',NULL),('Senior HSEQ Trainer','Qatar','Doha','','About the job Senior HSEQ Trainer\nResponsibilities  Provide training and assessments as needed to meet the specific needs of course participants, and employ appropriate training techniques to achieve positive learning outcomes. Aiming for >90% course participant evaluation results  Contribute to the development of industry training packages, ensuring that in-house training meets the competency and capability assessment frameworks defined by relevant industry standards and accrediting bodies\' competency assessments.  Conduct course participant evaluations and determine compliance with pre-requisite criteria in accordance with key client requirements.  Assist in the development, modification, and enhancement of training materials as needed to ensure the accuracy and relevance of training Ensure that internal training meets or exceeds principles like \'ISO/IEC 17024 Conformity Assessment - General requirements for bodies operating certification of persons,\' Industry Standards, and accrediting bodies competency assessments.  Provide satisfactory training reports of course participant evaluation to allow department and business unit managers to act on any areas identifie