arios covers all requirements Review and analyze test results to determine the cause of the discrepancy and communicate with the team Generate test reports from the automated test executions Determine performance testing models to be used and validate them Identify inadequacies and improvement opportunities in the methods/standards and recommend changes Requirements Candidate should possess a technical Diploma / Bachelor\'s degree in Computing/Information Technology or related field Possess good analytical and troubleshooting skills Should have at least 3 years of experience in software development and/or testing Experience in automated testing tools such as Selenium and Micro Focus UFTExperience in web service testing tools such as Postman and Soap UIExperience in performance testing tools such as Micro Focus Load Runner and JMeter Good understanding of software development Proficient in testing and development methodologies Good verbal and written communication skill Ability to work effectively in a team or independently Good To Have Comfortable with fronting client Ability to conduct user acceptance testing with users Experience in Agile development environments Experience in test management tools such as Micro Focus ALMExperience in test automation frameworks such as Cucumber and Karate',NULL,'2023-10-12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'DXC.technology',NULL),('Financial Consultant','Egypt','Cairo','Nasr City','Be the customer\'s primary point of contact for product-related issues and build and maintain a relationship with the customer over email or phone/conference calls. Resolve customer questions and inquiries by identifying problems, researching answers, collaborating with vendors/other team members and delivering solutions to problems or creating appropriate workarounds. Provide end-to-end complex application support for issues logged in the ticketing system Perform gap analysis between a client\'s requirements and the System functionality  Asse