ecurity best practices and ensure compliance with industry standards and regulations. Regularly perform security assessments and vulnerability management. Automation and Scripting: Develop and maintain automation scripts and tools to streamline operational tasks. Automate routine maintenance and backups. Collaboration and Documentation: Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including developers, QA, and IT operations, to align Dev Ops efforts with business objectives. Create and maintain documentation for infrastructure, processes, and procedures. Incident Response and Troubleshooting: Participate in incident response activities, troubleshoot issues, and implement solutions to minimize downtime. Establish and maintain disaster recovery plans and procedures.','2023-11-01',0,0,3,7,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Easy Cash',NULL),('Information Security Engineer','Egypt','Cairo','Heliopolis','Assists in developing, updating, publishing, maintaining, communicating and enforcing Info Sec policies, procedures, and standards. Researching information security standards based on business strategies and requirements. Provides Info Sec policy training and awareness. Major role in developing Info Sec Audit program to measure policy compliance. Performs Risk Assessment and provides recommendations for remediation. Performs security controls effectiveness assessments. Maintaining the Info Sec Program documentation.',NULL,'2023-10-25',1,2,4,10,30000,60000,0,2,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Easy Cash',NULL),('Senior Backend Developer (PHP)','Egypt','Cairo','Heliopolis','Key Responsibilities: Backend Development: Implement server-side logic, databases, and applications. Ensure the development team follows best practices in coding and architecture. Project Management: Manage and prioritize the team\'s workload, ensuring timely project delivery. Collaborate with other teams, including frontend development, to ensure seamless integration of server-side and client-side components. Quality Assurance: Implement quality assurance processes to maintain the high quality and reliability of server-side components. Perform code reviews and ensure adherence to coding standards. Scalability and Performance: Optimize server-side components developed in PHP for performance and scalability, addressing any bottlenecks or issues. Proactively identify and resolve technical challenges to maintain optimal system performance. Security: Implement and enforce security best practices in server-side development to protect against potential vulnerabilities. Ensure data protection and compliance with security standards. Technical Expertise: Stay current with industry trends and emerging technologies in PHP to make informed decisions and recommendations. ','Job Description: We are in search of a highly skilled Backend Senior Developer for our dynamic development team. your responsibilities will encompass designing, building, and maintaining server-side logic, databases, and applications critical to the success of our software projects. Job Requirements: Education: Bachelor\'s degree in computer science, software engineering, or a related field. A Master\'s degree is a plus. Experience: Minimum of 5 years of experience in backend development with a deep focus on PHP , Technical Skills: Deep expertise in PHP for backend development. Profound expertise in PHP for backend development, with a strong emphasis on Laravel and/or Yii. Strong knowledge of database systems, including SQL and No SQL databases (e,g, Postgre SQL, Mongo DB...etc.). Experience with microservices architecture and containerization (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes). Familiarity with data streaming platforms and queuing systems(e.g. Rabbit MQ, Kafka ). Knowledge of integrating with logging systems (e.g., ELK, syslog). Experience with in-memory data stores like Redis for caching and data storage. Proficiency in using JIRA for task management, time estimations and issue tracking. Experience with workflows in JIRA is highly desirable. Quality and Security: Understanding of software quality assurance and security best practices. Experience with code reviews, testing, and compliance with security standards. Problem-Solving: Strong problem-solving and analytical skills to address complex technical challenges. Scalability: Experience in optimizing server-side components developed in PHP for scalability and high performance. Certifications: Relevant certifications are a plus. ','2023-11-01',0,0,4,6,NULL,NULL,1,3,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Easy Cash',NULL),('Senior Software Quality Engineer','Egypt','Cairo','Heliopolis','  Key responsibility : Requirements Evaluation: Diligently review requirements, specifications, and technical design documents. Provide timely and constructive feedback to enhance software quality. Test Planning: Craft comprehensive, well-structured test plans that encompass every facet of our products. Develop clear and detailed test cases to facilitate thorough testing. Test Coordination: Efficiently estimate, prioritize, plan, and coordinate testing activities, ensuring alignment with project deadlines. Types of Testing: Perform diverse testing methodologies, including: Functional Testing: Validate that the software functions as anticipated. Smoke Testing : quick test to check if essential functions of a software build are working. It\'s done to ensure the software is stable before more detailed testing. Integration Testing: Verify the seamless interaction between different components and services. Regression Testing: Confirm the stability of the software after resolving bugs. Black-Box Testing: Assess software from a user\'s perspective to validate its functionality. API Testing: Validate the reliability and functionality of APIs. Security Testing: Scrutinize the software\'s security features to identify and rectify vulnerabilities. Performance Testing: Evaluate system performance and scalability to ensure optimal functionality. Testing Processes: Innovatively develop and apply testing processes for new and existing products, adapting to evolving client needs and the ever-changing industry standards. Collaboration: Forge seamless collaboration with internal teams, including developers and product managers, to identify and validate system requirements. Quality Metrics: Rigorously monitor and track quality assurance metrics, such as defect densities and open defect counts, to drive continuous improvements in software quality.  ','Requirements: Experience: A minimum of 5 years of relevant software quality assurance and/or control experience. Programming Knowledge: A strong grasp of fundamental programming concepts. Knowledge of Programming languages such as Python or Java are preferable Proven Experience: Demonstrated work experience in software quality assurance/control, highlighting your ability to maintain high software quality standards. Methodologies and Tools: Profound knowledge of software QA/QC processes, methodologies, tools such as Soap UI, Postman, Load Runner, JMeter ...etc. Automation: Proficiency with automated testing tools such as Selenium/Appium. Agile Development: Experience working in an Agile/Scrum development process, ensuring alignment with team goals and objectives. Specialized Skills: Experience with performance and/or security testing is a valuable asset, particularly in the fintech sector. Fintech Background: Prior experience with fintech applications is a significant advantage.','2023-11-01',NULL,NULL,5,8,NULL,NULL,1,3,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Easy Cash',NULL),('Java Developer - Back End','Egypt','Cairo','Nasr City','Collaborate with the rest of the team to design and launch new features. Maintain code integrity and organization. Understanding and implementation of business, security and data protection. Highly experienced with back-end JAVA programming language and Spring framework. Can continue working on other developers code.','Highly experienced