Test Management software (JIRA, TFS, ALM). Solid experience with Defect Management Process. Quick learner and self-starter who requires minimal supervision to excel in a dynamic environment. Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills. Strong verbal and written communications skills. Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science or related field. Experience in MS SQL server, SSIS and SSRS. Awareness of Agile QA Software development life cycle –backlog, sprints, standups, burn downs','2023-10-22',6,1,2,4,NULL,NULL,1,4,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'eT3 - Tomorrow Information Technology',NULL),('Full Stack .Net Developer','Egypt','Giza','Mohandessin','We are looking for a skilled Full Stack . NET Developer to join our team. The ideal candidate will have experience developing web applications using . NET  technologies and a strong understanding of Microsoft SQL Server. Responsibilities Design, develop, and maintain web applications using . NET technologies Develop and maintain Angular applications Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify and prioritize features Write high-quality, testable, and efficient code Troubleshoot and debug issues in existing applications Develop and maintain Microsoft SQL Server databases Keep up-to-date with emerging trends and technologies If you are a motivated who is passionate about technology and looking for a challenging opportunity, we would love to hear from you.','Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science or related field At least 2 years of experience in developing web applications using . NET  technologies Experience with Javascript and JQuery Experience with Microsoft SQL Server Knowledge of web development best practices, including responsive design and cross-browser compatibility Experience with Git, Azure Dev Ops, or similar version control systems Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills Strong communication and interpersonal skills Familiarity with Angular is a plus Familiarity with ABP Framework is a plus','2023-09-01',89,15,2,4,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Ether Technology',NULL),('Computing Teacher','Egypt','Giza','Sheikh Zayed','We’re looking for Computer Teacher to teach our students about computers and how to use them. The ideal candidate will have experience teaching students of all ages and be able to engage them in learning. If you are a Computer Teacher who is excited about teaching and willing to work with students to help them succeed, then we want to hear from you!','Proven experience as a teacher Excellent spoken and written English Thorough knowledge of teaching best practices partnered with a willingness to follow the school’s policies and procedures Excellent communication skills Well-organized and committed Creative and energetic Strong moral values and discipline','2023-10-01',3,0,2,10,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'Ethos International School',NULL),('FSTD Quality Engineer','United Arab Emirates','Abu Dhabi','',' Synopsis Implement technical quality control measures which ensure that EAT flight simulation equipment continues to meet both training and regulatory requirements while achieving industry leading levels of reliability. Accountabilities QTG review management, validation & quality control.\nFSTD Flight Test planning, logistics, implementation, reporting.\nFSTD Flight Test Quality Control (reporting & defect recording).\nFSTD Visual Model Check planning, implementation & Visual Model database management.\nSimulator updates and modification management + Load release.\nDefect clearance - planning, logistics, implementation, reporting.\nLiaising with Manager Simulator Maintenance to manage and implement Regulatory Evaluations & Audits.\nPlanning & implementation of FSTD Inspections and investigation.\nPlanning & logistic support for EASA FSTD Qualification visits.\nImplementation of software and hardware configuration control, including integration and acceptance of manufacturer delivered software.\nProviding simulator and aircraft subject matter support to the simulator maintenance team during the investigation of simulator system and hasrdware problems.\nSupporting simulator quality control activities by working closely with project pilots and other subject matter experts to ensure training equipment objective and subjective performance continues to meet both regulatory and training requirements.\nEducation & Experience Educated to an appropriate bachelor’s degree or national equivalent.\nMinimum 5 years of experience working with Flight Simulator Training Devices.\nHands-on working experience on FSTD qualification requirements (QTG, SFT, Configuration control etc).\nKnowledgeable on Regulatory requirement, procedures, and documentation.\nAbout Etihad Aviation Training Based in Abu Dhabi and part of ADQ Aviation & Aerospace Services, Etihad Aviation Training (EAT) is an Approved Training Organization (ATO) located in the capital of the United Arab Emirates Abu Dhabi. EAT provide an extensive portfolio of aviation training courses and programs covering all areas of pilot, cabin crew and airport operations. The courses vary from Ab-initio pilot license, Airbus and Boeing type ratings, instructor and examiner training, cabin crew training, English Language Proficiency testing, First Aid. With the recent inclusion of Gulf Center for Aviation Studies (GCAS), one of a few centers globally accredited by the International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO), Airports Council International (ACI) and the International Air Transport Association (IATA), EAT offer includes training programs focused on Airport Operations, Aviation Safety, Aviation Security, Cargo & Dangerous Goods, and non-aviation training such as Health & Safety, Leadership & Management, Soft Skills. EAT’s training center is approved by several Civil Aviation Authorities including GCAA (UAE), EASA (Europe) and QCAA (Qatar). Training at EAT is conducted by using its state-of-the-art training center featuring 10 Full-Flight Simulators (Airbus and Boeing), 7 Flight Training Devices and 2 Flight Navigation Procedural trainers.',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Etihad Airways',NULL),('Inventory Analyst','United Arab Emirates','Abu Dhabi','',' Synopsis Analyze technical inventory data and assist in setting controls on the same to support part’s availability, prepare dashboards, KPI (Key Performance Indicators) and perform operational data analysis to aid Senior Inventory Analyst in taking data driven inventory recommendations. Accountabilities Extract data and prepare KPI and operational dashboards to monitor supply chain performance.\nReview inventory accuracy and recommend corrective actions to improve data quality in ERP.\nGenerate inventory levels recommendations for consumable & rotable parts.\nInventory report preparation and variance analysis with finance reports.\nSupport senior analyst in preparing inventory holding strategies and implementation. \nPrepare and track actual technical spend vs. Budgeted spend.\nCoordinate with surplus customers and generate optimum revenue from sale of surplus parts.\nSupport in developing processes & departmental manuals and keeping them up to date and in compliance with regulators and organizational requirements. \nSupport Audits and any ad hoc project assigned to achieve department goal.\nEducation & Experience Bachelor’s or equivalent technical degree and a minimum of 3 years of experience in supply chain data analytics & inventory management, preferably within aviation industry.\nGood understanding of aviation ERP inventory and materials management modules, preferably AMOS.\nExpert level knowledge in Microsoft Excel, Power BI, and Oracle SQL (preferred).\nStrategic & tactical thinking, analytical mind and cost management experience are required.\nPreferred to have understanding of aviation parts & supply chain functions.\nA resilient candidate with ability to adapt to different and multicultural environments & work under pressure.\nSelf-motivated team player and excellent written & verbal communication skills. \nAbout Etihad Airways Etihad Airways, the national airline of the UAE, was formed in 2003 and quickly went on to become one of the world’s leading airlines. From its home in Abu Dhabi, Etihad flies to passenger and cargo destinations in the Middle East, Africa, Europe, Asia, Australia and North America. Together with Etihad’s codeshare partners, Etihad’s network offers access to hundreds of international destinations. In recent years, Etihad has received numerous awards for its superior service and products, cargo offering, loyalty programme and more. Etihad is recognised as one of the world’s leading airlines in response to COVID-19 and was the first airline in the world to fully vaccinate its crew on board. Etihad sees tackling the climate crisis as the most important issue of our time, and through strategic partnerships with major global aviation brands and OEMs, Etihad is relentless in its pursuit of industry decarbonisation. To learn more, visit etihad.com',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Etihad Airways',NULL),('Manager Network Revenue Optimization','United Arab Emirates','Abu Dhabi','',' Synopsis As Etihad continues to grow its network and fleet, we have an incredibly exciting opportunity to join our Revenue Division in a pivotal role; Network Revenue Optimization Manager. In this role you will lead a cross-functional team to develop and implement Etihad’s revenue optimization strategy. You will collaborate with Revenue Management leadership to develop and implement revenue maximizing with JV & Alliance partners. You will review and provide inputs to global business cases created by network planning for structural and seasonal changes to the Etihad network. Accountabilities Corroborate with RM teams to build route strategies in co-ordination with S/MMs to introduce/implement new routes/frequencies to the Network, measure performance & update senior leadership.\nLead review of business cases created by network planning for structural and seasonal cases with Regional RM teams\nNegotiate and challenge any Network Planning assumptions and provide alternative assumptions\nContinuously monitor Network performance for incremental revenue opportunities\nIdentify gaps between and EY & partner carriers and co-ordinate with RM/NP teams to minimize these and capitalize on opportunities\nSupport strategic evaluations related to fleet configurations and hub structures\nCreate plans that identify and prioritize partners within Alliances portfolio that maximize enabled revenue\n Build strategies for management and monitoring of network revenue performance of Codeshare and Alliance partners\nDeliver and present performance reviews of revenue contribution from tactical or structural activity   \nProactively build revenue assumptions for RM driven network opportunities and consult with Network Planning for options.\nCalendarize network peak periods and conduct scheduled reviews with SMMs / Heads for periods of absolute peak demand & events. Recommend actions to further enhance network revenue performance.\nBe the focal point of contact with Network Planning teams for any revenue estimations.\nEducation & Experience Minimum Bachelors’ degree, preferably Business or Engineering (post-grad. qualifications an advantage)\nMinimum of 5 years’ experience within either Network Planning, Revenue Management or Alliances with deep understanding of Pricing and Inventory\nAbout Etihad Airways Etihad Airways, the national airline of the UAE, was formed in 2003 and quickly went on to become one of the world’s leading airlines. From its home in Abu Dhabi, Etihad flies to passenger and cargo destinations in the Middle East, Africa, Europe, Asia, Australia and North America. Together with Etihad’s codeshare partners, Etihad’s network offers access to hundreds of international destinations. In recent years, Etihad has received numerous awards for its superior service and products, cargo offering, loyalty programme and more. Etihad is recognised as one of the world’s leading airlines in response to COVID-19 and was the first airline in the world to fully vaccinate its crew on board. Etihad sees tackling the climate crisis as the most important issue of our time, and through strategic partnerships with major global aviation brands and OEMs, Etihad is relentless in its pursuit of industry decarbonisation. To learn more, visit etihad.com',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Etihad Airways',NULL),('Senior Data & Analytics Specialist','United Arab Emirates','Abu Dhabi','',' Synopsis In this role, the candidate will support the Global Sales team to connect and correlate data points from the different systems to draw strategic insights. The ideal candidate will be an action-oriented analyst who uses critical thinking and advanced analytical techniques to support the development of optimum Sales strategies. He/she will also actively work with sales team and support teams on development and maintenance of reports, dashboards and sales forecasting models; and own and manage multiple data initiatives and projects both on an on-going and an ad-hoc basis, while using new approaches of data analytics. Accountabilities Support the development & execution of core sales data/reports/dashboards \nExecute quantitative analyses of data and trends to proactively deliver insights, define goals, and drive program improvements.\nExecute solutions to business problems using data analysis, data mining, optimization tools, statistical modelling and machine learning techniques\nCreate and ideate bespoke solutions and dashboards to empower operational and exploratory analysis. \nDevelopment of new data models and management of Reference data. \nManagement of sales data system inputs and data quality\nSummarize / visualize results and highlight insights & opportunities for sales teams\nEducation & Experience Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Operations Research, Economics or Business Administration\n3+ years working experience in a complex numerate and analytical environment, experience within airline industry preferred\nDemonstrated experience in manipulating and analysing complex, high-volume, high-dimensionality data from varying sources to highlight patterns and relationships.\n2+ years of experience using database querying tools and ability to write complex queries using Azure, SQL and/or Microsoft SQL\n2+ years of experience in any of visualization tool (Pow er BI, Tableau, Spotfire, etc.\nProven knowledge of Microsoft Office and minimum 2+ years of hands on experience of scripting tools like R, Python\nWell-developed analytical and problem-solving skills with solid experience in business analysis, and at least 2 of; segmentation, regression analysis, clustering, forecasting, web analytics\nAbout Etihad Airways Etihad Airways, the national airline of the UAE, was formed in 2003 and quickly went on to become one of the world’s leading airlines. From its home in Abu Dhabi, Etihad flies to passenger and cargo destinations in the Middle East, Africa, Europe, Asia, Australia and North America. Together with Etihad’s codeshare partners, Etihad’s network offers access to hundreds of international destinations. In recent years, Etihad has received numerous awards for its superior service and products, cargo offering, loyalty programme and more. Etihad is recognised as one of the world’s leading airlines in response to COVID-19 and was the first airline in the world to fully vaccinate its crew on board. Etihad sees tackling the climate crisis as the most important issue of our time, and through strategic partnerships with major global aviation brands and OEMs, Etihad is relentless in its pursuit of industry decarbonisation. To learn more, visit etihad.com',NULL,'2023-10-27',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Etihad Airways',NULL),('Senior Inventory Analyst','United Arab Emirates','Abu Dhabi','',' Synopsis Set controls on the technical inventory to support part’s availability and Service Levels for Technical operations in the most cost-effective manner. Lead a team of inventory analysts to ensure all aspects of inventory management, such as operations support, investment analysis, surplus management and inventory oversight are maintained and organized across the team. Accountabilities Publish KPI (Key Performance Indicators) and operational dashboards to monitor supply chain performance.\nMonitor inventory accuracy and liaise with respective stakeholders to improve data quality in ERP.\nAnalyze inventory levels for consumable & rotable parts and provide recommendations to respective stakeholders.\nEnsure inventory report preparation and variance analysis with finance reports.\nDevelop inventory holding strategies and classify active, surplus, excess inventory. \nSupport annual budget preparation and monitor budgeted vs. actual spend.\nDevelop, establish and manage relationships with surplus customers and ensure optimum revenue is generated from surplus sales to meet target.\nSupport in developing processes & departmental manuals and keeping them up to date and in compliance with regulators and organizational requirements. \nSupport Audits and any ad hoc project assigned to achieve department goal.\nEducation & Experience Bachelor’s or equivalent technical degree and a minimum of 5 years of experience in supply chain data analytics & inventory management preferably within aviation industry.\nGood understanding of aviation ERP inventory and materials management modules, preferably AMOS.\nExpert level knowledge in Microsoft Excel, Power BI, and Oracle SQL (preferred). \nStrategic & tactical thinking, analytical mind and cost management experience are required.\nPreferred to have understanding of aviation parts & supply chain functions.\nA resilient candidate with ability to adapt to different and multicultural environments & work under pressure.\nSelf-motivated team player and excellent written & verbal communication skills. \nAbout Etihad Airways Etihad Airways, the national airline of the UAE, was formed in 2003 and quickly went on to become one of the world’s leading airlines. From its home in Abu Dhabi, Etihad flies to passenger and cargo destinations in the Middle East, Africa, Europe, Asia, Australia and North America. Together with Etihad’s codeshare partners, Etihad’s network offers access to hundreds of international destinations. In recent years, Etihad has received numerous awards for its superior service and products, cargo offering, loyalty programme and more. Etihad is recognised as one of the world’s leading airlines in response to COVID-19 and was the first airline in the world to fully vaccinate its crew on board. Etihad sees tackling the climate crisis as the most important issue of our time, and through strategic partnerships with major global aviation brands and OEMs, Etihad is relentless in its pursuit of industry decarbonisation. To learn more, visit etihad.com',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Etihad Airways',NULL),('NOC Senior Engineer','Egypt','Giza','6th of October','§ Handling Enterprise customer’s technical problems. § Receiving customer complaint via Mail, call and customer portal. § Effective communication in handling hard calls for frustrated customers. § Making first troubleshooting on customer connection. § Solving customer Trouble Tickets as FCR.§ Escalating Trouble Tickets which not solved as FCR to concerned team with providing appropriate solution.§ Working to escalate the repeated problems to finalize it permanently. § Following and finalizing Key Accounts customers’ problems. § Handling customer high level internal network technical requests. § Handling complex routing complaints with 2nd level NOC. § Handling complex configuration modifications from both Provider & customer edges requested from customers. § Supporting NOC support coordinator by Handling customers’ night emergency technical change requests (TCRs) § Supporting NOC support coordinator by Handling non-technical complaints and requests during night shift. § Supporting NOC support coordinator by following Call Back during night shift. Operation Target: § Working to achieve First Call Resolution target. § Achieve them queue SL (80/20). § Achieving routing / configuration changes SRs SL. § Achieving SRs SL and escalation time § Working to enhance NPS score. Customer Experience: § Handling customer’s emails professionally. § Adhering to call standards in order to provide excellent service to our customers. § Handling queue SRs and requests.','§ B. Sc. in Communications Engineering § CCNA certified.§ Very Good Knowledge in networking solutions and services. § Very good writing and reporting skills. § Very good communication skills.§ Very good in English language. § Ability to work under stress and pressure. § MS knowledge is required. § Flexibility in terms of working hours.§ CCNP Certified § Cisco Routing Certified§ Previous experience within ISP Providers preferred.§ CCNA Certificate § Cisco Routing Certificate § Soft Skills','2023-10-17',5,0,0,1,7000,8000,0,10,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Etisalat Egypt',NULL),('System Senior Specialist','Egypt','Cairo','New Cairo','Job Purpose The Senior Systems Administrator will be responsible for the configuration, implementation, and maintenance of various technologies managed by the Information Technology department. He should ensure the efficient and reliable operation of the systems and maintain their availability and reliability. Report To Position Name Administer operation systems through all IT infrastructure and platforms. Prepare reports and ensure optimal service availability Ensure efficient maintenance and ensure compliance to all disaster recovery plans. Provide latest access security to protect all infrastructure services. Monitor all communication for each customer to assess operations within timeframe. To assure highest level of systems availability and to maintain the data integrity, security and best systems performance. To plan and develop the backup strategies assuring the best data recovery time. To be responsible for the configuration, and maintenance of various technologies managed by the Information Technology department. He should ensure the efficient and reliable operation of the systems and maintain their availability and reliability. Maintain records of all service level agreements for customers. Check and ensure resolution of all issues to achieve all operations objectives without breaching the SLA. Enhance operations SLAs and assure customer satisfaction. Responsible of any upgrade patches across production systems and ensure quality and standard. Apply patch fixes for all bugs on all live systems whenever needed. Administer all infrastructure services and provide backup for recovering systems. Ensure SYSTEM availability of all systems and IT network application. Provide backup and redundancy to retrieve data in case of emergency. Restore a random services/databases on regular basis to ensure backup healthy state Have a solid backup process with documentation of the data type, location, size, date and time, RBO and RTO for auditing purposes. Enhance the Systems Performance to assure using the server resources in the most effective and efficient way. Enhance the database Security to support the data confidentiality and privacy. Plan and implement the systems upgrades and patches installation to assure of using the latest available technologies and avoiding the known bugs. Administer all network equipment, hardware (routers, switches, wireless access points, voice servers, gateways and IP phones) and software upgrades. Design and maintain all IT processes according operation policies through standardization of methods. Maintain and 