ze our codebase for quality and scalability Enhance our practice in continuous integration, test automation and other state of the art practices Collaborate with other team members and stakeholders Mentor junior members of the team to grow our skill base','What skills do you need?You have the capacity to work autonomously in a rapidly changing and sometimes ambiguous environment You have previous experience (4+ years) developing server-side solutions at considerable scale You\'ve worked with any JVM language before We\'re confident that great engineers can quickly get up to speed, and we\'ll provide the support and time you need to do that We offer: Competitive Salaries Hybrid working environment Paid time off Healthcare coverage A highly collaborative team environment that will support your professional and personal growth A culture of learning and innovation Office located at Maadi, Cairo Our technical team is led by Khaled Nassef, the Co-Founder & CTO of Flap Kap. Khaled comes with more than 10 years of experience working in reputable tech companies like Amazon Web Services (AWS) and German Fin Tech unicorn, N26. You can check more details about Khaled through his Linked In profile https://www.linkedin.com/in/knassef/','2023-11-01',NULL,NULL,4,8,NULL,NULL,1,2,'Experienced (Non-Manager)',NULL,'FlapKap',NULL),('IT Help Desk Coordinator','Egypt','Giza','6th of October','Serve as the first point of contact for employees seeking technical assistance over the phone or email. Installing and upgrading hardware and software systems. Perform  troubleshooting through diagnostic techniques. Running software diagnostic tools and physically inspecting hardware systems. Provide quick and effective assistance with information technology systems.','Bachelor’s degree in computer science, computer engineering.1- 3 years of experience. Very good communication skill, problem-solving skills. Very good command in English.','2023-09-01',72,24,1,3,NULL,NULL,1,1,'Entry Level (Junior Level / Fresh Grad)','Bachelor\'s Degree','FlexFilms Egypt',NULL),('Associate Project Controls Specialist II','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Associate Project Controls Specialist IIJubail Eastern Province Saudi Arabia Diversity Statement At Fluor, we are proud to design and build projects and careers. This requires teams that are as unique as the projects we execute. We are committed to fostering a work environment that embraces Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (DE&I) for all so our employees and stakeholders benefit from the creative solutions derived as a result of embracing differences. Job Description This position performs fundamental Project Control activities. • Understand the scheduling and cost terminology • Apply the principles of a Work Breakdown and Project Coding Structures to schedule/cost data to ensure that the data are correctly and consistently entered into the Project Controls System • Implement procedures for a project scheduling/cost program • Collect data, input updates, and produce basic cost/scheduling management reports • Ensure efficiency and accuracy in generating and gathering data; maintain orderly records to ensure the integrity of the system • Use Project Controls reference systems as primary tools for executing responsibilities • Other duties as assigned Notice to Candidates: Background checks are carried out as part of any conditional offer made, including (but not limited to & role dependant) education, professional registration, employment, references, passport verifications and Global Watchlist screening. To be Considered Candidates: Must be authorized to work in the country where the position is located. Basic Job Requirements• Accredited four (4) year degree or global equivalent in applicable field of study and one (1) year of work-related experience or a combination of education and directly related experience equal to five (5) years if non-degreed; some locations may have additional or different qualifications in order to comply with local requirements • Ability to communicate effectively with audiences that include but are not limited to management, coworkers, clients, vendors, contractors, and visitors • Job related technical knowledge necessary to complete the job • Ability to learn and apply knowledge of applicable local, state/province, and federal/national statutes and guidelines • Ability to attend to detail and work in a time-conscious and time-effective manner Preferred Qualifications• An accredited four (4) year degree or global equivalent technical degree or non-technical degree with business and computer software courses • Advanced degree (Masters or global equivalent) preferred • Possess strong personal computer skills • Proficiency in the use of automated cost/schedule management systems • May need to travel internationally for project assignments and in support of business related matters Requisition Number141893BRDiverse Workforce We are an equal opportunity employer that recognizes the value of a diverse workforce. All qualified individuals will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, age, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, religion, national origin, disability, veteran status, genetic information, or any other criteria protected by governing law.  Associate Project Controls Specialist II | Fluor Corp',NULL,'2023-10-23',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Fluor Corporation',NULL),('Certifying Engineer - B1','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','Completion and certification of scheduled and un-scheduled maintenance tasks on the operated fleet. Supervision of maintenance teams as required KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES  Key Activities 1. To ensure that all maintenance is carried out in accordance with flydubai and regulatory requirements. This will be achieved by making full use of the resources made available by flydubai and in keeping up to date with latest issues of all forms of support documentation.     2. To ensure that certification of tasks is carried out only within the limitations of the company issued approval. This will require a comprehensive knowledge of the flydubai Procedures.      3. To ensure that all maintenance is carried out to the highest standards and within the operational limitations prescribed. This means that all maintenance is to be carried out in accordance with the manuals and documentation provided by flydubai.  4. Completion of Work Packages as allocated. To ensure that all Work Packages are completed thoroughly and the relevant AMOS entries are made. To endure that any damage identified is recorded correctly and concisely. 5. Assisting with the recovery of AOG aircraft, to support down route requirements when requested. To ensure that the job holder has their passport at work at all times and that the required inoculations are kept up to date.   6. Raising Parts Requests for ADD as required. When raising an ADD and the spares required are known, the job holder is required to ensure that all associate spares are ordered and that AMOS and the ADD Sheet in the Technical Log is annotated accordingly.    7. Assisting with overtime requirements as requested. This will include both voluntary and rostered overtime totaling up to 50 hours per calendar month.        8. Assist the Team Leader Line Maintenance as required. When allocated Teams and/or tasks by the Team Leader Line Maintenance, the job holder will carry out their duties accordingly.    9. Deputize for the Team Leader Line Maintenance as required. This will require a comprehensive knowledge of the role of the Team Leader Line Maintenance.    10. To retain currency on all Licenses and Authorizations issued by Regulatory Authorities and flydubai Quality Assurance. This entails having an awareness of the expiry dates of all Licenses and Authorizations and making sure that renewals are applied for in a timely manner so as to ensure that currency is maintained.  Qualifications MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS / EXPERIENCE/ KNOWLEDGE / SKILLSMinimum Qualification•Current Part 66 B1 Aircraft Maintenance Engineers License (or FAA/ICAO equivalent) with ratings on the Boeing 737NG and CFM56-7B engine.     Experience•Demonstrated experience in the maintenance of Boeing 737NG in a Line and Base Maintenance environment Knowledge / Skills•Broad knowledge and experience in the use of IT systems including Microsoft Suite and MRO Systems.  CORE COMPETENCIES•Above average skills in effective communication.•Excellent understanding of written and spoken English.•Excellent Team Worker.•Demonstrated levels of shown initiative, recognizing shortfalls and addressing them without being asked  •Demonstrated ability to think logical•Demonstrated ability in Operational and Situational Awareness•Demonstrated ability an analytical approach to Trouble Shooting •Safety and Airworthiness Awareness ISR Requirements Reads and complies with the ISR policies of the Company and diligently reports any weakness or incidents to the respective Line Manager or the Information Security team. Completes all required ISR awareness sessions and follows associated guidelines in the day to day business operations. ',NULL,'2023-10-15',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'flydubai',NULL),('Senior Analyst - Financial Planning & Control','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','MAIN OBJECTIVE OF ROLETo  prepare various MIS reports including short/long term projections, network performance, route performance and adhoc analytical improvements. KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES Key Activities Prepares various MIS reports including adhoc requirements: ensuring accuracy, timeliness and value addition to Management decisions.\nAnalyzes and drafts monthly and quarterly network performance compared to budget and previous year, with revenue and cost variances.\nPrepares weekly, monthly and quarterly route performance reports compared to budget and previous year, and report to management.\nWorks closely with the business to highlight current performance and future trends for management.\nReviews center performance and key KPIs and presents findings to Business Units.\nReviews and presents a performance summary of the approved business case to all stakeholders.\nSupports the team in monthly closing activities and the annual budgeting exercise.\nProvides key inputs towards system enhancements and integration.\nServes as a ‘financial consultant’ to the Engineering department.\nReviews and provides feedback on Engineering vendor agreements.\nReviews and monitors all purchase requests against the budget and providing necessary approvals in line with the published Authorities Manual.\nQualifications MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS / EXPERIENCE/ KNOWLEDGE / SKILLSMinimum Qualifications Bachelors Degree  (or equivalent) \nEducation Specific Requirements Accounting Degree, Computer Application Diploma or certification,\nExperience Specific Requirements Preferred No. of Years (with Relevant Degree) - 5\nPreferred No. of Years (without Relevant Degree - if applicable) - 8\nCORE COMPETENCIESCustomer Focus\nTeam work\nEffective Communication\nPersonal Accountability & Commitment to achieve\nResilience and Flexibility (Can do attitude)\nISR Requirements\nReads and complies with the ISR policies of the Company and diligently reports any weakness or incidents to the respective Line Manager or the Information Security team. Completes all required ISR awareness sessions and follows associated guidelines in the day to day business operations.',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'flydubai',NULL),('Senior Analyst (Vendor Management) – IT PMO & Partnerships','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','To effectively oversee data collation, cost validations, and vendor payments, in addition to managing Opex/Capex resources, related project account activities, monitor project execution and foster vendor relationships in alignment with the organizational objectives of the IT Demand Management team. KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES Key Activities Oversees the management of Opex/Capex resources, including the timely initiation of Purchase Requests (PRs) and Purchase Orders (POs). \nEnsures prompt vendor payments, encompassing around 45,000 person-days of resource utilization.\nSupervises the execution of Turnkey and Fixed Bid projects awarded to our development partners, ensuring their successful delivery within scope, budget, and timelines.\nManages the financial aspects of the IT Opex portfolio, including budget tracking, cost optimization, and financial reporting.\nConducts monthly Business and Technology Service reviews with vendors and fosters collaborative relationships, addresses concerns, and drives continuous improvement.\nMonitors and reports on the status of payments to vendors, ensuring adherence to Service Level Agreements (SLAs) and payment credit periods. \nCollaborates closely with Procurement and Finance teams to secure timely approvals and payments.\nDevelops and maintains key performance indicators (KPIs) to assess vendor performance, service quality, cost-effectiveness and implements improvements based on data-driven insights.\nEnsures that vendors comply with contractual obligations and meets the established performance standards, promptly addressing any discrepancies or non-compliance.\nIdentifies and mitigates risks associated with vendor relationships, including potential cost overruns, service disruptions, or contractual disputes.\nCollaborates with stakeholders to select and onboard new vendors, ensuring alignment with organizational goals and standards.\nSeeks opportunities proactively for process optimization, cost reduction, and operational efficiency within the vendor management framework.\nMaintains effective communication with internal stakeholders, including IT teams, Procurement, Finance, and Business Units, to align vendor management activities with organizational objectives.\nConducts regular vendor performance assessments and provides constructive feedback to enhance service delivery.\nQualifications MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS / EXPERIENCE/ KNOWLEDGE / SKILLSMinimum Qualification Bachelor’s Degree (or equivalent)\nEducation / Experience Specific Requirements Degree in Statistics or Business Data Science (preferred)\nStrong knowledge and experience in airline technologies, systems and processes.\nPreferred No. of Years (with Relevant Degree) - 5\nPreferred No. of Years (without Relevant Degree - if applicable) - 8\nSystems, Licensing, Language or Certification Requirements PMP certification (PMI) or Prince II Certification\nCORE COMPETENCIESCustomer Focus\nTeam work\nEffective Communication\nPersonal Accountability & Commitment to achieve\nResilience and Flexibility (Can do attitude)\nISR Requirements Reads and complies with the ISR policies of the Company and diligently reports any weakness or incidents to the respective Line Manager or the Information Security team. Completes all required ISR awareness sessions and follows associated guidelines in the day to day business operations.',NULL,'2023-11-01',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'flydubai',NULL),('Senior Officer – Commercial Systems','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','MAIN OBJECTIVE OF ROLETo enhance the Revenue Management ecosystem by supporting continuous research and implementation of transformation projects, exploring revenue opportunities, preventing revenue leakages and driving the automation of routine processes. KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES Key Activities Provides recommendations based on trends in market conditions relative to competitor activities, political / economic trends / industry developments.\nEngages constantly in problem solving activities for continuous system improvements.\nDesigns and implements SMART processes into the system.\nTakes full ownership of maintenance, development, and scalability of the current commercial systems.\nActs as the focal point in discussion with key stakeholders (including IT and business teams) to implement and rollout changes to commercial systems while ensuring minimum downtime.\nPlays an integral role in the revenue planning process, which delivers revenue targets and forecasts to the sales force.\nEstablishes strategies aimed at reviewing the efficiencies and effectiveness of models and algorithms developed to maximise revenue.\nMentors and guides a team of commercial system officers.\nQualifications MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS / EXPERIENCE/ KNOWLEDGE / SKILLSMinimum Qualifications Bachelor’s Degree (or Equivalent)\nEducation / Experience Engineering / Finance / Statistics / Accounting / Economics / Mathematics\nPreferred No. of Years (with Relevant Degree)- 7\nSystems, Licensing, Language or Certification Requirements Knowledge of SQL/Oracle/Access and / or statistical tools\nCORE COMPETENCIESCustomer Focus\nTeam work\nEffective Communication\nPersonal Accountability & Commitment to achieve\nResilience and Flexibility (Can do attitude)\nISR Requirements\nReads and complies with the ISR policies of the Company and diligently reports any weakness or incidents to the respective Line Manager or the Information Security team. Completes all required ISR awareness sessions and follows associated guidelines in the day to day business operations.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'flydubai',NULL),('Senior Officer Airport Services – DXB & DWC','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','To provides support, leadership and coaching to the front-line staff engaged in ensuring the smooth and efficient processing of all passengers, ensuring the consistent application of the company’s commercial and safety and security standards, policies and procedures KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES\n Key Activities\n Organizes allocation of agents to check-in, Departures/Transfer, Ramp or Arrivals on a rotating basis and provide briefings on a shift by shift basis.\nManages and controls manpower on the shift, in order to optimize utilization and to maintain staff morale and discipline, and acting as supervisor in absence of same.\nResolves customer problems and complaints while on duty and working with all departments including customer to provide resolutions.\nMonitors assigned area of passenger and ramp handling to achieve and maintain the highest customer service standards at check-in/boarding gate/ramp and arrivals.\nEnsures proper enforcement of flight opening/closure times, baggage policies, Credit Checks and documentation requirements.\nLiaises with NCC and GHA and organize staff to ensure timely commencement and close out of boarding process. \nEnsures safe passenger embarkation and disembarkation processes and monitor turn-round handling and baggage handling activities within company/regulatory safety and security regulations.\nChecks post-flight documents, telex, prepare reports and check sheet for accounting purposes.\nMonitors Service Partners/Providers performance against flydubai’s SLAs and ensure they are adhering to safety and security regulations and to flydubai processes and procedures.\nLiaises with all stakeholders and assists passengers in case of delays or disruption.\nMonitors, examines/investigates and reports any discrepancies, irregularities or operational problems (e.g. delays) in day to day activities and identify & implement solutions.\nQualifications MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS / EXPERIENCE/ KNOWLEDGE / SKILLS\n Minimum Qualification Bachelors Degree or equivalent \nExperience5 years relevant experience with degree\n7 years relevant experience without degree\n \nAdditional Requirements\n Experience in areas such as passenger services, baggage services, ground handling operations, dangerous goods regulations and Ramp handling.\n \nCORE COMPETENCIES\n Customer Focus\nTeam work\nEffective Communication\nPersonal Accountability & Commitment to achieve\nResilience and Flexibility (Can do attitude)\nInspiring & Developing Others\nDecision Making\n \nISR Requirements Reads and complies with the ISR policies of the Company and diligently reports any weakness or incidents to the respective Line Manager or the Information Security team. Completes all required ISR awareness sessions and follows associated guidelines in the day to day business operations.',NULL,'2023-10-19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'flydubai',NULL),('Senior Software Engineer – RPA','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','To optimize business processes through the implementation of Robotic Process Automation (RPA), by working closely with various departments to identify automation opportunities and to design and develop RPA solutions ensuring the efficient execution of automated tasks. KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES Key Activities Collaborates with business analysts, process owners, and stakeholders to understand business requirements, identify automation opportunities, and design RPA solutions that meet business needs.\nDevelops, tests, and implements RPA workflows and bots using RPA software platforms such as Ui Path and Automation Anywhere. \nWrites efficient and maintainable code to automate repetitive tasks and processes.\nIntegrates RPA solutions with existing systems and applications, ensuring seamless data flow and communication between the RPA bots and other systems.\nConducts thorough testing of RPA solutions to identify and resolve issues, ensuring the reliability and accuracy of automated processes.\nCreates detailed documentation, including process workflows, technical specifications, and user manuals, to support the deployment and maintenance of RPA solutions.\nMonitors the performance of deployed RPA bots and proactively address any issues or errors. Implements improvements and updates as necessary to optimize the efficiency of the automation.\nEnsures that RPA solutions adhere to security and compliance standards and best practices and implements necessary security measures to protect sensitive data.\nCollaborates with cross-functional teams, including IT, operations, and business units, to identify new automation opportunities and gather feedback for continuous improvement.\nProvides training and support to end-users and junior engineers on RPA best practices and troubleshooting techniques.\nContributes to the development and future update of a flydubai ‘Software Engineering Playbook’ and other standards documents adhering to best practice coding standards, guidelines, and documentation.  \nQualifications MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS / EXPERIENCE/ KNOWLEDGE / SKILLS Minimum Qualification University Degree or equivalent\nEducation / Experience Specific Requirements Information Technology, Computer Science, or related field \nProven experience as a software engineer with a strong focus on RPA development\nProficiency in one or more RPA platforms such as Ui Path or Automation Anywhere\nStrong programming skills in languages such as Python, C#, or Java\nKnowledge of process automation, workflow design, and business process modeling\nFamiliarity with integration techniques and APIs\nRelevant certifications in RPA technology are a plus\nPreferred No. of Years (with Relevant Degree) - 5\nSystems, Licensing, Language or Certification Requirements Certifications in Ui Path or Automation Anywhere RPA technologies are recommended\nCORE COMPETENCIESCustomer Focus\nTeam work\nEffective Communication\nPersonal Accountability & Commitment to achieve\nResilience and Flexibility (Can do attitude)\nISR Requirements Reads and complies with the ISR policies of the Company and diligently reports any weakness or incidents to the respective Line Manager or the Information Security team. Completes all required ISR awareness sessions and follows associated guidelines in the day to day business operations.',NULL,'2023-10-18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'flydubai',NULL),('Software Engineer','United Arab Emirates','Dubai','','To design, develop, implement, and maintain software-based technology and products that provide support across flydubai. KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES Key Activities Executes a complete Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC), from requirement analysis and solution design, to coding, unit testing, integration while supporting  quality assurance and user acceptance testing.\nDevelops software solutions that complies with flydubai coding standards and technical design ensuring  the output is a well-designed, testable code.\nWorks with the Software Technical team to understand the functional and non-functional requirements  and technical design. \nLiaises with the IT Corporate & Support team  to understand the various business scenarios and requirements across flydubai to create prototypes in alignment with each department.\nDevelops software verification plans and quality assurance procedures and executes unit test cases, debugs, to resolve the defects. \nIntegrates software components into a fully functional software system and performs System Integration Tests (SIT). \nDocuments the user manual, product release and technical documentation for software maintenance.\nProvides ongoing support and guidance to the business post go live and provides technical support, evaluating any user feedback for future releases/fixes.\nEnsures the development cycle meets the software development KPIs, in terms of productivity, defect density and system performance.\nCollaborates within the software engineering community, share experiences, learns new frameworks, and develop new skills.\nWorks with the Learning & Development team to upgrade software development skills. Sets targets to achieve periodic certifications and keep abreast on new tools and technologies. \nContributes to the development and future updates to the repositories  adhering to best practice coding standards, guidelines, and documentation.\nQualifications MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS / EXPERIENCE/ KNOWLEDGE / SKILLSMinimum Qualification Bachelors Degree or equivalent\nEducation / Experience Specific Requirements Information Technology, Computer Science, or related field\nProficient in programming languages such as C#,. Net \nThorough understanding of Object-oriented concepts\nMust have experience in working with database applications such as SQL Server, No SQL, Oracle\nFamiliar with . Net related software & technologies (Kafka/IBM MQ/Web API/RAML integration techniques, APIs, design patterns, algorithms, software version controlling Agile development methodologies and the latest web technologies).\nPreferred No. of Years (with Relevant Degree) - 3\nCORE COMPETENCIESCustomer Focus\nTeam work\nEffective Communication\nPersonal Accountability & Commitment to achieve\nResilience and Flexibility (Can do attitude)\nISR Requirements Reads and complies with the ISR policies of the Company and diligently reports any weakness or incidents to the respective Line Manager or the Information Security team. Completes all required ISR awareness sessions and follows associated guidelines in the day to day business operations.',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'flydubai',NULL),('Corporate Sales Account Manager','Egypt','Cairo','Maadi','\'Approach Each Customer With The Idea Of Helping Him Or Her To Solve A Problem Or Achieve A Goal, Not Of Selling A Product Or Service.” – Brian Tracy Basically, what we are looking for is a sales wizard with the ability to build a relationship with our client and provide them with the best-fit solutions. What we need you to do : Build long-term relationships with existing, as well as, new clients. Identify growth opportunities and potential deals within our market segments. Increase revenue and retention rate for your accounts through approaching and upselling Ensuring that customer requests are responded to in an accurate and timely manner. Help the business meet sales and revenue goals. Negotiation and planning for short and long-term subscriptions. Align with cross-functional teams to meet clients’ expectations.','What you need to have: Previous experience in sales is a must, but it will be nice if it was B2B sales Ability to approach people and understand their needs Passionate about helping others Multi-tasking will be a great asset to you It will be also a huge advantage for you if you worked on a CRM before. ','2023-10-03',13,1,2,5,NULL,NULL,1,5,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Forasna',NULL),('Assistant F&B Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','',' Job Description:\nOur client stands tall in Riyadh\'s vibrant F&B scene, known for its distinctive dining outlets that cater to a diverse clientele. Main Objective:\nSupport the F&B Manager in overseeing the operations, ensuring efficiency, quality, and guest satisfaction across all outlets. Character Profile:\nAn enthusiastic and driven professional with a keen eye for detail and a proactive approach to challenges. Responsibilities and Duties: Operational Support: Assist in managing the day-to-day operations of F&B outlets. Guest Relations: Address guest feedback promptly, ensuring consistent satisfaction levels. Team Coordination: Work closely with the F&B teams, ensuring effective communication and task execution. Inventory Management: Monitor stock levels and assist in the procurement process. Reporting: Prepare regular reports on sales, guest feedback, and staff performance. Qualifications: A Bachelor\'s Degree in Hotel Management or a related field. Over 6 years of experience in F&B operations with a minimum of 2 years in a supervisory role. Strong organizational, interpersonal, and problem-solving skills.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('Data Governance Manager','Qatar','Doha','',' Job Description:\nOur client is a progressive diversified and sustainable business group in the region providing an outstanding experience in the Automotive and Associated Businesses through superior value products and services in partnership with some of the worlds leading brands. They are looking for a Data Governance Manager to join their team. The Data Governance Manager will be leading the data governance team in the formation and execution of data governance framework, policies, and standards. Moreover, ensuring that data quality requirements are defined, documented, and translated into effective and consistent processes that improve the quality of data. Duties & Responsibilities Manage and embed Data Quality projects/ initiatives that will deliver tangible data quality improvement through root cause analysis, data cleansing etc.\nEstablish and govern an enterprise data governance implementation roadmap that is aligned with company\'s strategic direction.\nRoll out a data governance framework, with a focus on improvement of data quality and the protection of sensitive data through modifications to organization behavior policies and standards, principles, governance metrics, processes, related tools and data architecture.\nDefine roles and responsibilities related to data governance and ensure clear accountability of corporate data systems.\nEnsure that the requirements for protecting sensitive data are clearly defined, communicated, and well understood and considered as part of operational prioritization and planning.\nFacilitate the development and implementation of data quality standards and data protection standards across the company.\nDefine indicators of performance and quality metrics and ensure compliance with data related policies, standards, roles, and responsibilities.\nIdentify new business opportunities pertaining to the use of information assets to achieve efficiency and effectiveness in the marketplace.\nRequirements Bachelors or masters in computer science, Information Systems, or other IT related field.\nMinimum 5 years in a senior management role with board level change or transformation leadership experience.\nStrong knowledge of industry leading data quality and data protection management practices.\nStrong knowledge of data related to government regulatory requirements and emerging trends and issues.\nInternally and externally recognized subject matter experts that influence the way things are done.\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('Event Project Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','',' Job Description:\nOur prestigious client, a renowned event management entity based in Riyadh, has embarked on a transformative journey, having secured a 5-year contract to manage international events for their local clientele. As they pave the way for world-class experiences, they are actively recruiting for an Event Project Manager to ensure impeccable execution and unparalleled experiences. Duties and Responsibilities: Lead the planning and execution of large-scale international events. Coordinate with clients to define event objectives and requirements. Develop detailed event project plans, including timelines, budgets, and resource allocation. Oversee cross-functional teams, ensuring tasks are completed on time and within budget. Liaise with international stakeholders, understanding their needs and ensuring local adaptability. Monitor event activities, ensuring the client\'s specifications are met. Resolve any arising issues or challenges promptly. Post-event, gather feedback and generate reports on event performance. Qualifications: Bachelor\'s degree in Event Management, Business, or related field.7+ years of experience in event management, with a focus on international events. Strong leadership and project management skills. Excellent interpersonal and negotiation skills. Proficiency in event management software.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('Executive Support Specialist','Qatar','Doha','',' Job Description:\nOur client is a progressive diversified and sustainable business group in the region providing an outstanding experience in the Automotive and Associated Businesses through superior value products and services in partnership with some of the worlds leading brands. They are looking to hire an Executive Support Specialist to join their team. To be successful in this role, the candidate must support the line manager in the achievement of objectives through providing high quality administration and project assistance, as well as preparing reports and presentations as requested. Duties & Responsibilities Format and produce high quality presentations that are visually appealing and effectively communicate key information. Proofread and edit presentations for accuracy and clarity. Gather information by researching, reviewing and evaluating data and documents related to the subjects under study, as directed by the direct line manager. Prepare a clear and concise report by synthesizing the findings, editing, and revising as necessary. Communicate and coordinate with the different departments for the completion and collation of data as instructed for projects, activities, etc. Draft important and confidential documents as needed. Plan, organize, and schedule meetings, record minutes of the meeting and disseminate MOM to the concerned. To liaise with external parties - vendors, and government authorities as per the requirement. Update the direct line manager on issues / queries that have to be followed up. Maintain the direct line managers\' calendar and facilitate travel arrangements. Manage the correspondence for the direct line manager i.e. organizing and sorting important emails, emails, etc. Maintain physical and e-records of confidential correspondence and documents. Carry out additional responsibilities and duties as assigned by the direct line manager and as per the department. Requirements﻿3+ years of experience as an Executive Support Specialist or other relevant administrative support roles Bachelors degree in any relevant field MS Office suite - Advanced level (Excel, Power Point, Word, etc.)High level of proficiency in English (reading, writing, and speaking)Strategic thinker, action oriented and results driven. Ability to take initiative and to develop/empower others. Communication and teamwork',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('Hard Services Manager','Qatar','Doha','',' Job Description:\nOur client is a leading Facility Management Company in Qatar that specializes in providing customized facility solutions and services to a diverse range of industries. They are looking to hire a Hard Services Manager to lead, Develop and implement operational strategies which lead to Company growth. Duties and responsibilities: Provide excellent service and meet or exceed client expectations and contract objectives. Identify opportunities to improve and expand the scope of services. Make recommendations to clients and management as appropriate. Monitor market trends and best practices. Provide insights and recommendations to improve quality and efficiency. Manage department budgets in accordance with company policies and guidelines. Continuously improve quality of service through innovations and implementation of best practices. Track performance metrics, monitor budgets, and prepare monthly reports for clients and senior leadership. Forecast budgets and expenses to ensure costs stay within approved levels. Oversee facilities management and ensure contract obligations are met. Consult with technical experts and senior leaders as needed to resolve issues and ensure smooth operations. Ensure compliance with health and safety policies, procedures, and legal requirements. Supervise staff and address personnel issues according to policies and procedures. Complete required audits and ensure quality standards are met. Provide training and development opportunities to staff to achieve business goals. Identify and manage risks associated with projects using appropriate controls and monitoring. Perform risk assessments and ensure staff are trained and compliant with requirements. Create reports and presentations for various audiences including staff, committees, and executives. Continuously improve facilities management services to deliver consistent high-quality outcomes. Perform additional duties as required within the scope of the role. Qualifications and competencies: Bachelor\'s degree or higher in Engineering, Facilities Management, or a related field Certifications: BICS, IOSH, HACCP, BIFM certified Quality Management System (ISO 9001) Occupational Health & Safety Management System (OHSAS 18001/ISO 45001) Certified Facility Manager (CFM, IFMA-USA) Extensive knowledge of current trends within the healthcare industry15-18 years of progressive experience in overseeing, supervising, and managing facility operations and staff ',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('Head of Research & Development','Kuwait','Kuwait City','',' Job Description:\nA vanguard in the healthcare sector, our client continually pioneers health solutions that redefine patient care in the Middle East. Main Objective:\nLead the R&D division, fostering innovation and translating groundbreaking research into tangible healthcare solutions. Character Profile:\nA visionary with an innate curiosity and passion for healthcare innovation. The ideal candidate thrives on challenges, constantly pushing the boundaries of what\'s possible in healthcare. Responsibilities and Duties: Innovation Leadership: Drive the ideation and development of innovative healthcare solutions. Collaborative Research: Foster collaborations with global research institutions, ensuring access to cutting-edge healthcare trends. Product Development: Oversee the translation of research into viable healthcare products or services. Team Mentorship: Lead and nurture a diverse R&D team, promoting a culture of continuous learning and innovation. Stakeholder Engagement: Engage with internal teams, ensuring the integration of R&D findings into the company\'s broader strategy. Qualifications: A Ph D in Biomedical Science, Medicine, or a related field. Over 10 years in healthcare R&D with a track record of significant innovations. Demonstrable experience in team leadership and project management. Strong networking, collaboration, and communication skills.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('IT Audit Supervisor','Qatar','Doha','',' Job Description:\nOur client is a progressive diversified and sustainable business group in the region providing an outstanding experience in the Automotive and Associated Businesses through superior value products and services in partnership with some of the worlds leading brands. They are looking for an IT Audit Supervisor who will be responsible of the following: Duties and Responsibilities: Develop and update Continuous Auditing (CA) Implementation Strategy. Further participate in the Implementation of Continuous Auditing, through the following: Deep understanding of the underlying business processes, application systems, and data sources. Identifying critical process risks & system control points, and prioritizing areas to be addressed. Designing technology-assisted approach to test controls and identify deficiencies. Designing analytic tests to measure or flag exception-based criteria. Managing the results (tracking, reporting, monitoring, and following up) in a master file. Capitalize on the experience learned and generated results by standardizing and consolidating CA test scripts in a designated library for IA team reference and knowledge sharing. Performs general and application control reviews for information systems. Performs IT security audits to include system development standards, network, operating system, data center, Information system security (including evaluation of security vulnerabilities and mitigation procedures), programming controls and cybersecurity audits. Other reviews associated with IT policies, change management, business continuity planning, backup and disaster recovery, and system maintenance. Follows up on audit / CA findings to ensure that management has taken corrective action(s). Assists and trains other audit staff in the use of computerized audit techniques, and in developing methods for review and analysis of computerized information systems. Maintains knowledge with respect to relevant state-of-the-art technology, equipment, and/or systems. Maintain and update SAP T-codes library to be aligned with IA departmental scope of work. Requirements University Degree in Information Technology / Computer Information Systems or related domain. Certification Information Systems Auditor (CISA) is a plus. At least 6 8 years of experience directly related to the duties and responsibilities specified. Strong ability to work effectively in a team and to communicate verbally and in writing with others. Strong analytical skills and ability to effectively prioritize and coordinate multiple tasks simultaneously. Background Knowledge in Continuous Auditing (CA)Knowledge of current technological developments/trends in area of expertise. Knowledge of auditing concepts and principles. Understanding of Information Security standards and best practices (e.g., ITIL Co BIT 2019)Understanding of Internal Audit standards and Internal Control environment.\n  Required Skills:\n\nBusiness Continuity\nMitigation\nAutomotive\nTest Scripts\nData Center\nInformation Security\nDisaster Recovery\nSAP\nAnalysis\nITIL\nInternal Audit\nAnalytical Skills\nInformation Systems\nReviews\nChange Management\nAuditing\nWriting\nProgramming\nInformation Technology\nStrategy\nSecurity\nMaintenance\nPlanning\nBusiness\nManagement\n',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('MLRO & Compliance Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','',' Job Description:\n Our client is one of the fastest growing fintech start-ups providing invoice discounting services in Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, they are looking to hire an MLRO & Compliance Manager for their Riyadh office. The role holder will be a detail-oriented and empathetic leader to head up Compliance and MLRO. Duties & Responsibilities Identifying compliance risks and advising on appropriate policies, procedures, systems, and controls. Documenting the organization, responsibilities and procedures of the Firms compliance function. Ensuring compliance breaches are readily identified, reported, and acted on. Keeping senior management up to date on changes in relevant regulations and their implications. Preparing the Firm for risk assessment visits. Reviewing the Firms marketing materials. Processing applications for the registration and withdrawal of individuals. Ensuring that employees receive training on what must or must not be done to ensure compliance. Liaising with the regulator and ensuring all regulatory returns and ad hoc notifications are submitted on\ntime. Maintaining the Firms regulatory files and registers. Providing support and training to the groups Compliance Officer where applicable. For MLRO: Identifying money laundering risks and advising on appropriate policies, procedures, systems and controls. Overseeing the day-to-day operation of the Firms policies, procedures, systems and controls. Receiving and investigating internal Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs) from employees. Reporting SARs to the Financial Intelligence Unit and to the regulator. Acting as the point of contact within the Firm for competent UAE authorities and the regulator. Overseeing compliance with UN sanctions and international, governmental and regulatory findings. Establishing and maintaining a staff awareness and training program for the prevention of money\nlaundering. Reporting to senior management on the quality and effectiveness of the Firms AML program. Requirements: 5+ years of Compliance experience in both Regulatory Compliance and the Financial Crime side. Previous senior Compliance Manager or MLRO responsibilities. Experience and familiarity with industry system providers and how to integrate providers into new and existing products and operational processes. In-depth and practical working knowledge of the compliance, money laundering and KYC decrees in Saudi Arabia. Experience working with international standards covering: Money Laundering Regulations, proceeds of financial crime, Bribery, Terrorism, Fraud, and other regulations impacting company\'s business. Previous experience in building teams and processes from scratch. Strong data, analytical and problem-solving skills. Ability to deal with problems in a practical and common-sense way, consistently demonstrating sound judgment. Preferably to have professional certifications for ICA or CAMS. ',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('Network Admin Support Lead','Qatar','Doha','',' Job Description:\nOur client is a progressive diversified and sustainable business group in the region providing an outstanding experience in the Automotive and Associated Businesses through superior value products and services in partnership with some of the world\'s leading brands. They are looking for a Network Admin Support Lead to join their team. The Network Admin Support Lead is responsible to manage the network support team in order to ensure the delivery of all the company\'s network and server system services to the users to sustain the business operation by overseeing, planning, and designing the strategies & coordinating with other team members (supervisor, manager) to align it in one common direction. Duties & Responsibilities Design, develop, install, configure, and maintain network operating system software and network infrastructure applications. Maintain software installation libraries, monitor directories and domains and audit server logs to identify performance issues and device failures. Install server fixes and service packs to maintain reliability and security. Troubleshoot, diagnose, and resolve server connectivity and performance issues, administer network standards including naming conventions and address protocols. Monitor, analyze and manage network traffic and other conditions to achieve optimal performance and uptime by analyzing data to minimize network congestion. Manage network support management team and coordinate with other IT team members to provide the network/server system services for business use. Define the KPIs of team members, evaluate resources and allocate tasks. Coordinate with data resource team and technical support team for optimizing the support service to users. Ensure the administration, backup/recovery, performance, and security of network/server system to comply service level agreement with the users. Maintain state-of-the-art computer room and peripherals. Analyze network capacity and growth requirements and recommend network infrastructure upgrades and enhancements to meet long-term the company needs. Develops plans for server room expansion including rack space, floor space, cooling and power requirements & installation of server racks, uninterruptible power supplies and other server support equipment. Develop specifications for network hardware, software and cabling upgrades and enhancements. Design, install and administer new security systems and methods. Create and maintains security rights on network resources, maintain and administer the firewall rule base and authentication systems, monitor for network intrusions and security breaches & implement and enforce the enterprise network security policy and remote access standards and guidelines. Research and evaluate hardware and software for compatibility, serviceability, design, and performance, Additionally, develop specifications and recommend the purchase of computer/network- related hardware and software. Monitor trends and developments in systems, networking and multi-platform communication technologies & consult vendors and other sources on industry and product direction, functionality, and capabilities. Requirements Bachelors in computer engineering Minimum 10 years relevant experience TCP/IP Networking and complex configuration.  Training / Certifications: CCNA, CCNP. TCP/IP Networking, CISCO Router/Switch and networking devices. ',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('RFP Specialist','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','',' Job Description:\nOur client is a premier event management company based in Riyadh. Their services include planning and organizing exhibitions, Gala dinners, conferences, summits, corporate events, fund raisers, product launches, networking events and festivals. They are seeking a skilled RFP Specialist to join their team in Riyadh. Job Brief: As an RFP Specialist, you will play a pivotal role in responding to RFPs and managing the proposal process for event-related projects. Your expertise in events management will be instrumental in crafting compelling and well-structured proposals that showcase our capabilities and services. Tasks and Duties: RFP Response: Receive and review incoming RFPs related to event management services. Analyze the requirements and scope of each RFP to understand client needs. Proposal Development: Develop customized and compelling proposals tailored to each RFP\'s requirements. Ensure proposals align with the company\'s event management capabilities and value propositions. Content Creation: Create well-written and persuasive content that showcases our events management expertise. Utilize case studies, success stories, and statistics to substantiate proposal claims. Collaboration and Coordination: Collaborate with sales, marketing, and event management teams to gather relevant information for proposals. Coordinate input and contributions from various departments to ensure a cohesive proposal. Proposal Formatting: Organize and format proposals to enhance readability and visual appeal. Utilize branding guidelines and templates for consistent presentation. Deadline Management: Ensure timely completion of proposals to meet RFP submission deadlines. Plan and prioritize tasks to manage multiple proposals simultaneously. Key Performance Indicators (KPIs): Proposal Success Rate: Measure the percentage of successful proposals that lead to project awards. Proposal Quality: Evaluation of the overall quality and effectiveness of submitted proposals. Proposal Timeliness: Percentage of proposals submitted within the specified deadline. Client Feedback: Gather feedback from clients on the quality and relevance of proposals. Skills and Qualifications: Bachelor\'s degree in Events Management, Marketing, Business Administration, or a related field. Proven experience in events management and a track record of successful event planning and execution. Previous experience in responding to RFPs and crafting winning proposals is a strong advantage. Excellent written and verbal communication skills with a keen eye for detail. Strong project management and organizational abilities to manage multiple RFPs simultaneously. Collaborative mindset and the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams. Familiarity with event industry standards and practices. Creative thinking and the ability to tailor proposals to specific client needs. Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite and proposal management tools. Time management skills to meet tight proposal deadlines.',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('Senior Account Director','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','',' Job Description:\nOur client is a marketing and communication agency based in Saudi Arabia offering a range of services such as advertising, events and many more. They are looking to hire a Senior Account Manager for their events department in Riyadh. Responsibilities: Serve as the primary point of contact for clients, vendors, and all other parties involved in assigned events. Develop strong relationships with clients to ensure repeat business and referrals. Understand client objectives and develop creative proposals that meet or exceed expectations. Negotiate contracts with vendors and service providers to secure the best possible terms and pricing. Manage event budgets and track all expenses to ensure accuracy and adherence to budget constraints. Create detailed event timelines and schedules to ensure all deadlines are met and all logistical details are accounted for. Oversee on-site event management and execution, ensuring all elements are carried out according to plan. Handle post-event follow-up, including thank-yous, surveys, and debriefs with clients and staff. Train and supervise junior event staff, providing guidance and mentorship as needed. Requirements: Bachelors degree in business, marketing, or related field8+ years experience in event management, with increasing levels of responsibility Excellent project management skills Strong budget development and oversight skills Superb written and verbal communication skills Outstanding organizational skills and attention to detail Fluent in Arabic and English',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('Senior Legal Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','',' Job Description:\nOur client is one of the fastest growing fintech providing invoice discounting services in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, and they are looking to hire a Senior Legal Manager for their Riyadh office. In addition to supply chain finance, our client will soon start offering B2B Buy Now, Pay Later, which would be the first of its kind offering in the region. The candidate should be comfortable working in a fast-paced environment with broad, generalist responsibilities, but with specialist legal subject skills in commercial law and regulatory matters pertaining to the financial sector. Duties and Responsibilities Give accurate and timely counsel to executives in a variety of legal topics (labor law, partnerships, international ventures, corporate finance etc.)Collaborate with management to devise efficient defense strategies Specify internal governance policies and regularly monitor compliance Research and evaluate different risk factors regarding business decisions and operations Apply effective risk management techniques and offer proactive advise on possible legal issues Communicate and negotiate with external parties (regulators, external counsel, public authority etc.), creating relations of trust Draft and Review agreements, contracts and other legal documents to ensure the companys full legal rights Deal with complex matters with multiple stakeholders and forces Provide clarification on legal language or specifications to everyone in the organization Conduct your work with integrity and responsibility Maintain current knowledge of alterations in legislation Able to liaise with SAMA and other agencies on licensing requirements and documentation. Requirements5-8 years\' experience in Corporate Law Have worked at least 6 years in a medium to large sized companies Proven experience as a Legal Manager in business environment Excellent knowledge and understanding of corporate law and procedures Full comprehension of the influences of the external environment of a corporation High degree of professional ethics and integrity Excellent communication skills (English is a MUST)BSc degree in Law or J. D. degree Previous experience in financial institutions or liaison with SAMA will be a big plus',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Foreground Consultancy',NULL),('Senior PR Account Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','',' Job Description:\nOur client is a marketing communication group with regional and local expertise in all aspects of marketing communications (Public Relations, Event Management, social media, and Public Speaking). They provide holistic Marketing Services to help them achieve their preset objectives. They are looking to hire multiple PR Account Managers to 