ts that generate more fee income. In conjunction with the functional head, formulate inputs and lead the implementation of the strategy in line with company\'s vision, mission and objectives. Manage the effective achievement of departmental objectives through the leadership of the department and the setting of individual objectives, recruiting qualified staff, managing performance, developing and motivating staff, provision of formal and informal feedback and appraisal in order to maximize staff and departmental performance. Support in the development of the department organization structure in order to ensure alignment with company\'s strategy and objectives. Ensure preparation/consolidation of budgets and monitor financial performance versus budgets, for the business to be aware of anticipated costs/revenues. Support the management of change through continuous improvement of departmental systems, processes and practices taking into account international leading practices. Develop and oversee the implementation of department policies, procedures and controls covering all areas of department activity so that all relevant procedural/legislative requirements are fulfilled while delivering a quality, cost-effective service. Ensure continuous efforts are exerted to contribute to the social environment of Kuwait society in all areas through company\'s CSR initiatives. Perform other related duties or assignments as directed. To be fully aware of our policies & procedures and CMA rules & regulations related to the work which are critical and can affect the work directly and indirectly. Requirements﻿﻿ Bachelors degree in Accounting, Finance, Economics or equivalent MBA/CFA is preferred 10 years of experience in a similar position with at least 4 years in a managerial position Ethics, compliance and professionalism Asset allocation and financial analysis Risk & financial management Engaging customers Developing talent Portfolio management',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NU