ription Configure and support cloud infrastructure solutions: Computing and storage. Identify and access management. Networking and security. Configure and support different security technologies such as: IDS and IPS. Fire Walls (Palo Alto, Frotigate and Cisco ….). SIEM, Antivirus, EDR solutions monitoring and analysis. DLP, NAC, Sandboxing, Web proxy, Mail security, VPN, MDM Solutions. Personal Skills Excellent organizational skills Very good communication, interpersonal and negotiation skills. Good relationship building and excellent team player. Good analytical skills. Excellent command of English Technical Skills• Cloud Administrator (AWS, Azure, OCI or GCP) or CCNA, Firewall administration Certificates is a plus • Very good using MS office and suitable typing speed Education• B. Sc. in computer science, computer engineering or relevant. Job Location Cairo, Egypt Job Role Engineering Years of Experience Min: 1 Max: 2 Residence Location Egypt',NULL,'2023-10-18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Giza Arabia Systems',NULL),('Senior Aris Developer','Egypt','Cairo','','Senior Aris Developer Job Description Work as a team member and identify and implement feasible architectural approaches. Perform unit testing and resolve defects in a development environment, maintaining the security of all system applications. Troubleshoot application issues, coding bugs, and bottlenecks. Work on dynamic data handling such as data pages, Change, triggers, and agents. Work on BPM workflow development, including UI components and tools. Provide reporting functions using Report Definitions, List Views, and Summary Views. Support internal architecture design: locking architecture, advanced agents, rule assembly, and execution. Meet with business managers to discuss t BPM application needs, and work with business architects, and system end-users. Personal Skills Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Engineering, or a related field. Having experience in performance optimization