pproachable manner Willingness to travel domestically and to work overseas Flexible and adaptable to a schedule that is dedicated by the fixture list and can change at short notice. We work whenever football happens, which means lots of weekends and evening matches A full valid driving licence is required and willingness to drive our vans Nice to have:  Experience working with video technology/replay technology desirable, or live event/technical production At Hawk-Eye Innovations, we appreciate and value the importance of potential and growth. If you do not hit all of the criteria above but believe that there are certain areas you excel in and that you possess the passion and desire to develop the other attributes, then we encourage you to apply.⚽Make an Impact in the World of Football Join our dedicated and dynamic team and help revolutionise the way technology is used in Football! As a Football Systems Operator, you\'ll gain invaluable experience and play a crucial role in some of the biggest Football events in the world.',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Hawk-Eye Innovations Ltd',NULL),('Football Systems Operator - Saudi Arabia, Jeddah','Saudi Arabia','Jeddah','','Location Saudi Arabia, Jeddah﻿﻿﻿﻿???? Location: The majority of work will take place on-site at football stadiums in Jeddah, with further opportunities for travel across Saudi Arabia and internationally???? Contract: Permanent, Full-Time???? Salary: Competitive???? Start Date: Immediate????*About the Role As a Football Systems Operator, you\'ll be responsible for setting up, monitoring, and operating our systems on-site at football stadiums in your region. You\'ll play a key role in the delivery of our services to SAFF, the AFC Champions League and major international tournaments like the World Cup. You will start out working on our Goal Line Technology and Semi Automated Offside services, but there will be the chance to gain exposure to various other services (such as VAR)