 to apply.⚽Make an Impact in the World of Football Join our dedicated and dynamic team and help revolutionise the way technology is used in Football! As a Football Systems Operator, you\'ll gain invaluable experience and play a crucial role in some of the biggest Football events in the world.',NULL,'2023-10-25',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Hawk-Eye Innovations Ltd',NULL),('Football Systems Operator - Saudi Arabia, Riyadh','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Location Saudi Arabia, Riyadh﻿﻿﻿﻿???? Location: The majority of work will take place on-site at football stadiums in Riyadh, with further opportunities for travel across Saudi Arabia and internationally???? Contract: Permanent, Full-Time???? Salary: Competitive???? Start Date: Immediate????*About the Role As a Football Systems Operator, you\'ll be responsible for setting up, monitoring, and operating our systems on-site at football stadiums in your region. You\'ll play a key role in the delivery of our services to SAFF, the AFC Champions League and major international tournaments like the World Cup. You will start out working on our Goal Line Technology and Semi Automated Offside services, but there will be the chance to gain exposure to various other services (such as VAR) as you grow in the role and become a more experienced member of the team. We will equip you with the technical training, assistance and full exposure to our systems to excel in this role.????Key Responsibilities Pre-match planning Setting up Hawk-Eye technology in the stadium (this can involve physically demanding work, such as rigging cameras and running cables) Conducting pre-match set up, checks and calibration of the systems in accordance with standard procedures Liaising with stadium staff, match officials and host broadcasters Monitoring the systems during the match Monitoring hardware and software performances, troubleshoot and report encountered issues Taking full ownership of our system on-site and being an ambassador for Hawk