aintain existing automation  (Jenkins, Bitbucket)Provide environments/operations triage support to troubleshoot & resolve build and deploy issues encountered in production, development, and test environments. Responsibility includes both workday and night/weekend on-call support as required to maintain the high availability of the applications for all users. Write clean, stable, and safe code in short time frames and frequent increments. Collaborate with Engineering and Operations teams to improve automation of workflows, infrastructure, code testing, and deployment. Work with software application developers to architect, configure, and troubleshoot application servers locally. ','Qualifications: The Perfect candidate must have a full experience of the following: Graduate from computer science, Engineering or any other related field.5+ Years of Experience as a Dev Ops Engineer Flexible with Working hours as he will work day and night. Linux Server Administration Docker Building, Running, and Configuration Apache and Nginx Server Configuration Large Scale My SQL Database Configuration, Maintenance, Replica, Backups, and restore AWS Cloud Services (Ec2, S3, ELB, Budgeting, Auto Scaling)','2023-09-01',1,2,5,NULL,1500,3000,0,1,'Experienced (Non-Manager)','Bachelor\'s Degree','Izam, inc.',NULL),('Senior Commercial Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Our People & Places Solutions business – reinforces our drive to improve the lives of people everywhere and epitomizes the \'why\' of what we do – the tremendous positive impact and value our solutions bring to our communities and society as a whole. From facilities delivering life-saving therapies and ensuring clean water to enabling the connection of people through all modes of transportation and providing access to technology – we\'re integrating a multitude of these solution elements to build the smart environments of tomorrow. Start your Jacobs career with a company that inspires and empowers you to deliver your best work so you can evolve, grow and succeed – today and into tomorrow.   Your Impact: Senior Manager Commercial Provide general direction to JACOBS in the Contract Management function   Prepare tender documents – tailored to JACOBS\'s needs n Utilization and allocation of resources for the global CM function  Provide guidance to Contract Management Discipline Managers.  Monitor operations within the limits of the approved budget n Maintain a relationship with the Functional Leaders of other functions to ensure the understanding of the objectives of the Service Lines and communicate them to other leaders and functional employees of the contract management area  Establish relationships with the management staff of the business units, to reach a mutual understanding of the objectives of the business unit and maintain communication in relation to the competencies necessary to achieve those objectives.   Ensure support in Contract Management for projects and operations of the business units, through the use of the latest tools and information available, facilitating the following: n Development and implementation of quality management programs to systematically improve Contract Management services n Provision of shared economic services, such as functional provider quality monitoring, expediting, and logistics services for use in all projects, when necessary Development and implementation of automated contract management systems n Approve the development and maintenance of an integrated plan that includes all Contract Management personnel to ensure uniformity and coordination of all measures, including: Methodology and approval of salary plans  Employee Performance Reviews and Career Discussions  Establishment and maintenance of a staffing, repatriation, planning and replacement system globally and across business unit lines.  Review and approval of planning for the development of practices, standards and policies for the Contract Management function n Maintain regular communication with business units to ensure services are adequate and effective.  Direct the development and approval of functional training programs to ensure that staff maintain a level of knowledge and skills sufficient to meet project requirements. n Approve development programs and consolidation initiatives with respect to contract management requirements  Prepare the salary plan for direct reports and approve salary plan recommendations for assigned departments. Provide guidance to the managers who report to him, for the planning and implementation of goals and objectives with a view to improving services. #QIDOpportunities Here’s What You’ll Need:',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Jacobs Engineering Group Inc',NULL),('Senior Commercial Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Job Description - Senior Commercial Manager (MID0002P6) Job Description Senior Commercial Manager - ( MID0002P6 ) Your Impact: Senior Manager Commercial Provide general direction to JACOBS in the Contract Management function Prepare tender documents – tailored to JACOBS\'s needs n Utilization and allocation of resources for the global CM function Provide guidance to Contract Management Discipline Managers. Monitor operations within the limits of the approved budget n Maintain a relationship with the Functional Leaders of other functions to ensure the understanding of the objectives of the Service Lines and communicate them to other leaders and functional employees of the contract management area Establish relationships with the management staff of the business units, to reach a mutual understanding of the objectives of the business unit and maintain communication in relation to the competencies necessary to achieve those objectives. Ensure support in Contract Management for projects and operations of the business units, through the use of the latest tools and information available, facilitating the following: n Development and implementation of quality management programs to systematically improve Contract Management services n Provision of shared economic services, such as functional provider quality monitoring, expediting, and logistics services for use in all projects, when necessary Development and implementation of automated contract management systems n Approve the development and maintenance of an integrated plan that includes all Contract Management personnel to ensure uniformity and coordination of all measures, including: Methodology and approval of salary plans Employee Performance Reviews and Career Discussions Establishment and maintenance of a staffing, repatriation, planning and replacement system globally and across business unit lines. Review and approval of planning for the development of practices, standards and policies for the Contract Management function n Maintain regular communication with business units to ensure services are adequate and effective. Direct the development and approval of functional training programs to ensure that staff maintain a level of knowledge and skills sufficient to meet project requirements. n Approve development programs and consolidation initiatives with respect to contract management requirements Prepare the salary plan for direct reports and approve salary plan recommendations for assigned departments. Provide guidance to the managers who report to him, for the planning and implementation of goals and objectives with a view to improving services.#QIDOpportunities Primary Location: Saudi Arabia-Saudi Arabia Countrywide-Riyadh-SA Riyadh - RYD - Legend Tower Job Posting: Oct 23, 2023, 4:08:38 PM Job: Legal/Contracts Administration Organization: PPS Job Type: Experienced Job Classification : Fulltime-Regular Work Locations: SA Riyadh - RYD - Legend Tower 8th floor Office No. 801-802, Bldg no. 8092, Legend Tower Riyadh 12313 Capabilities : Cities and Places',NULL,'2023-10-26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Jacobs Technology Inc.',NULL),('MEP Package Lead','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Description JASARA Program Management Company is seeking a highly skilled professional to join their team as the MEP Package Lead. In this role, you will be responsible for overseeing the MEP (mechanical, electrical, plumbing) package for some of the most exciting and complex programs in the world. You will have the opportunity to bring visible change within the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, working with a team of inspired professionals who are dedicated to reaching new levels of performance excellence. Responsibilities To lead the delivery of the MEP package in delivering the key objectives of; Safety, Health and Wellbeing, Environmental, Programme inclusion of published milestones, Budget, Quality, Client Requirements Support the procurement cycle in the lead up to Contracts being awarded. Lead the mobilization period with all MEP suppliers ensuring and assuring that all “set to work” activities are completed. Ensure and assure that Supplier Contracts are administered as per the Contract Conditions. Liaising with the governance bodies and all stakeholders. Management of the ecosystem in the delivery of the program objectives. Work closely together with the QA/QC team to ensure traceability of all completed works. Co-ordinate closely with all parties in a multi-D fashion integrating the MEP package with all other packages and works. Where appropriate monitor MEP key performance indicators and where appropriate develop new monitoring measures. Liaise with (sub)contractors to ensure all permits are issued without negative effect in the works. Liaise and coordinate with the requirements management team to assure the requirements derived from their processes are properly traced, managed, followed and validated. Represent the construction/delivery team in the corresponding meetings and workshops. Work together with the safety, construction and lifting team to keep high standards of safety on the site. Be an active member by leading, coordinating or supporting client in the event of accidents or incidents Requirements Previous experience in package management of construction projects. Excellent knowledge in the field of MEP works. Good understanding of the construction constraints and priorities during the construction activities. Good skills in the identification and evaluation of the risks associated with his field. Good reading and understanding of the “big picture” Achievement drive/Outcome focused Digitally orientated * Knowledge and awareness of task/activity control measures Construction methodologies and sequences',NULL,'2023-10-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Jasara Program Management Company',NULL),('Senior Quality Manager','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Description JASARA PMC, a joint venture between Public Investment Fund (PIF), Jacobs, and Saudi Aramco established to elevate the delivery of Social Infrastructure programs in Saudi Arabia, is currently seeking a Senior Quality Manager. As a Senior Quality Manager, you will be responsible for overseeing and monitoring the quality control activities of contractors working on this critical project. Responsibilities Develop and implement a comprehensive Quality Management Plan (QMP) for the project. Conduct regular inspections, walkthroughs and surveillances to ensure compliance with quality control standards of all civil work activities. Ensure effective resolution of non-conformance/non-compliance issues through proper documentation and corrective/preventive action. Participate in the development of contracts and scopes of work. Build and develop relationships with contractors, vendors, suppliers, and stakeholders to ensure quality requirements are being met. Provide technical assistance and guidance regarding quality control to personnel assigned to the program. Participate in audits and assessments of both internal and external quality systems. Requirements Bachelor\'s degree in civil engineering or related field 15+ years of experience in quality management within the construction industry Experience in managing large-scale civil engineering projects. Excellent communication skills and the ability to work collaboratively with internal and external stakeholders. Thorough understanding of quality control management systems, standards, and codes Ability to travel to various project locations within Saudi Arabia* Knowledge of industry-standard software and tools used in quality control management systems.',NULL,'2023-10-19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Jasara Program Management Company',NULL),('Testing & Commissioning Manager (Systems MEP) - THE LINE','Saudi Arabia','Riyadh','','Description JASARA PMC, a leading program management company is seeking a talented Testing & Commissioning Manager (Systems MEP) to join our team on THE LINE project. As the Testing & Commissioning Manager, you will play a crucial role in ensuring the successful implementation and delivery of this groundbreaking initiative. The Testing & Commissioning Manager is responsible for maintaining contact with stakeholders, maintaining a close knowledge of project requirements for commissioning and testing, assisting in resolution of issues, coordination and liaison with designers, consultants, contractors and stake holders through meetings, project procedures and reports; supporting and supplementing various Project Managers and the Contracts department to reduce the backlog of outstanding design/engineering action issues, coordination issues, and outstanding variation instructions to be prepared and issued to the Contractors. The position provides for maintaining of the access to records, manuals and technical literature, test reports, project data bases, drawings and the like. The Testing and Commissioning manager is responsible for the staging and operational implementation sequencing to ensure the city-wide systems are brought into use in the most effective and efficient methods. Liaison with design is key to ensure any Commissioning requirements are designed in the systems in the early stages of conceptual development. Responsibilities The role is to provide T&C leadership for the Systems Package Team, and the T&C Engineers who are responsible for:  Interface with Health and Safety for Process, Procedure, and implementation of on-siteworks. Design Reviews (for constructability) Engineering Support for Design ensuring Commissioning sequencing is considered. Implementation / Operation integration within Neom-The Line Modules Engineering support for Commercial / Budget Allocation Commissioning Oversight and Management Commissioning Delivery Schedule and Programme Quality Assurance Processes• Leading Test & Commissioning strategy Ensuring safe delivery methods and construction delivery by Contractors with adequate site supervision. Monitor schedules and responsibilities for FAT / SAT and any offsite testing, routine testing, witness testing. Develop and submit testing and commissioning reports, progress reports. Requirements Bachelor\'s degree in Mechanical or Electrical Engineering, or a related field. 15 years of experience – ability to demonstrate major projects experience (Testing and Commissioning) at senior level Preferably Chartered Engineer status and/or Project Management accreditation Technical awareness of the following systems, which will deployed as part of the MEP and Cognitive City architecture: Electrical Power Systems, Digital Systems commissioning, Control system integration, Telecoms communication systems. Strong experience in organisation co-ordination. Integration and package management (through supply chains) * Complex stakeholder and interface management experience',NULL,'2023-10-22',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,NULL,'Jasara Program Management Company',NULL),('Junior IT Specialist','Egypt','Giza','Abu Rawash','Junior IT Specialist Offer expertise in software development and engineering. Write and test software as per specifications and designs. Review 