he Contract\nThis is a Home Office position based in Dubai, but it may involve occasional visits to the Client offices and/or site in Iraq\nReporting to the Engineering Manager engineer the candidate will assume sole responsibility for assigned Instrument and Controls engineering work scopes\nTo carry out Instrument and Controls discipline work within a project team, supporting the project team for field development of oil and gas production facilities\nTo plan, budget, organize, and control a segment of the Instrument and Controls engineering deliverables for the project\nTo prepare Instrument and Controls deliverables for all project Phases the oil and gas industry\nTo ensure that all work is completed without compromise to quality and is delivered according to the project schedule\nTo provide direction and guidance on all Instrument and Controls engineering technical queries raised by either internal or external parties\nTo liaise with the Client’s Engineering, Operations and Maintenance staff as required to ensure a consistent approach to project completion\nTo promote safe behaviour at all times\nTo provide sound technical advice and solutions to a diversity of technical problems within the discipline\nTo co-ordinate with other disciplines during all stages of design development, construction, pre-commissioning, and start-up\nTo assist in the coordination of all activities related to Instrument and Controls engineering design\nTo identify any areas of concern with respect to progress and/or quality and recommend corrective actions as required\nThorough knowledge and understanding of the fundamentals of Instrument and Controls engineering design and analysis\nThorough awareness of relevant international codes and standards\nFamiliar with the typical software packages that are used for Instrument and Controls engineering design\nExperience of the application of HAZOP, HAZID and SIL Rating to Instrument and Controls design\nExperience with Instrument and Controls 