erables and ensure that they conform to all applicable engineering codes and standards as well as the Client’s policies and procedure\nEnsure that the overall project is delivered to meet the asset operational need\nProvide direction and guidance on all technical queries relating to pipeline design and engineering\nParticipate in all project safety and design reviews as necessary\nEnsure that all work is completed without compromise to quality and is delivered according to the project schedule\nLiaise with the Client’s Engineering, Operations and Maintenance staff as required to ensure a consistent approach to project completion\nPromote safe behaviour at all times\nProvide sound technical advice and solutions to a diversity of technical problems within the discipline\nCo-ordinate with other disciplines during all stages of design development, construction, pre-commissioning, and start-up\nProvide technical support to site in terms of material inspection, Factory Acceptance Testing, etc.\nAssist in the coordination of all activities related to pipeline deliverables\nIdentify any areas of concern with respect to progress and / or quality and recommend corrective actions as required\nAttend weekly progress meetings and generate status reports for the Engineering / Project Manager\n\nSkills / Qualifications\nDegree in Mechanical Engineering (B. Sc./B. Eng./M. Sc.)\nMembership of a recognised professional institute preferred\nMinimum of 15 years experience in the oil and gas industry\nRelevant years of experience required in ADNOC Sour Gas FEED projects.\nMinimum of 6 years proven capability in an engineering design company\nFamiliar with the typical software packages that are used for pipeline design and selection\nExperience working with multi-national and multi-cultural project teams is strongly preferred\nPrevious experience of working in the Middle East would be an advantage\nThorough knowledge and understanding of the fundamentals of pipeline design and analysis\n